					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4220048">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rikjard-regreps" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2750540); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2750540&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252525" alt="Rikjard Regreps" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2750540)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rikjard-regreps" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2750540); return false;" >Rikjard Regreps</a></span> <span class="odate time_1555354889 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Apr 2019 19:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4220048">
									

<p>Well, firstly some specific points and questions:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Some&nbsp;specific&nbsp;questions/points.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Specific&nbsp;points</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>footmen</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Why, if I may ask? What purpose do they serve? Also, it has been pointed out to you that 4R does not, and never had, footmen.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>RH/4R</p>
</blockquote>
<p>RH?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Normally the language would've settled the age question, but this was a Bavarian going by the accent. There wasn't much to expect in the way of proper speech.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Accent? If I understand correctly, he is speaking german, right? So he would not have an accent, maybe a dialect.<br />
Also, why that dismissal of bavarian capability for proper speech?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Boy,&quot; Salz's hand moved to the collar of his overcoat, pulling it back just enough to display the symbol tattooed on the side of his neck. &quot;Are you pure of heart?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is that meant to imply that Salz has the 4R-symbol tatooed on his neck? In a normally visible fashion? The Fourth Reich takes great pains to ensure that their symbol cannot be seen by the naked eye unless anomalous means are taken. They usually do their best to keep a low profile.</p>
<p>Also, I have to question the validity of openly asking what is a kinda obivous phrase to recognize one another. If that was a member of the Fourth Reich, even f in the area on other matters, Salz would have been informed to prevent misunderstandings?</p>
<p>Also, the use of a codephrase to recognize allies is something that would not be needed in an organisation as small as 4R (usually) is, which brings me back to the question of why add footmen. Thereby making such things (which, if used on a foudation agent could lead to discovery of their current activities) necessary.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>His Snitch and Witness, those wretched surveillance unterdaemons he dragged everywhere, were perched in the far corner as lookout,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&#8230; Fels never summons demons. He neither has the necessary abilities to get them over to the mortal plane, nor does he have any desire to have any contact with demons. His forte are plants and animals and using his abilities to manipulate/change them.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Still, Acolyte Fels remained motionless. Was this his idea of self-perfection? Sitting in a cloud of burnt plants and dust? All he perfected was burning out his sense of smell. Salz clapped, and again, Fels remained still.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Fels is not a calm enough person to sit still and ignore it when someone interrupts him.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>another faint rustle of leaves as Fels stood up</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&#8230; is he wearing pants made out of leaves?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Acolyte Fels wasn't particularly tall at 165&#160;cm</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Where did you get that information from?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Need I remind you of Blitz?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Blitz wasn't a snitch, rather a deserter. He got fed up and simply left.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A sharp cough from Fels silenced the Snitch. &quot;Acolyte Salz, if you will.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Am I getting this correctly: Whenever Salz gets angry, it becomes painful/harder to breath around him? Why would Rass tolerate someone who is a constant danger to everyone around?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>THIS FAG BASHES BACK</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In german there is no shorter version for that word, so if thats supposed to be written in german it would be correct to use the full word.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Fats Burg</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That name sounds very fake to me, so the reveal that it is fake doesnt really hold much&#8230; anything, really.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I also have some more general points:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">General&nbsp;questions/points.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">General&nbsp;points</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>How does AWCY know about 4R? How did they learn about them? The foundation had four of its creations in containment before it figured anything about 4R out, and even then luck was on their side.</p>
<p>Sorry for running that point into the ground, but I really dont see the point of adding footmen.</p>
<p>The word &quot;degenerate&quot; is used a lot in this tale. Only this word (by which I do mean its german translation) is extremely rarely used in german. Overall Herr Rass and 4R prefer the word &quot;unclean&quot;.</p>
<p>What potential does a conflict between AWCY and 4R hold? I admit, I dont know much about AWCY, but afaik they are art terrorists. Why would they try to engage in war with a group like 4R which can make use of demons that can single-handedly wipe a trained MTF out?<br />
Also, what is so important about the muse-bug-thing that 4R wants it, thereby risking conflict with another GoI? Which is something 4R wants to avoid because they prefer to keep a low profile until the time comes to put their bigger plans into motion.</p>
<p>The kind of demons the Fourth Reich uses would never be something anyone in their right mind would keep around. Because they tend to be smart, powerful, and have their own agenda. Those demons who aren't are too insignificant to be of interest to 4R.</p>
<p>I think that all the stuff AWCY pulls in the middle of a city in this story would get the foundations attention very, very quickly.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Bottom line: This &#8230; does not read like it involves 4R. Switching out the names and a few terms would suffice to make this into a different group. The biggest problems in my opinion are:</p>
<ul>
<li>A purposely small organsations which consists of Rass, Acolytes, and anomalies now suddenly has footmen</li>
<li>An Acolyte with &quot;leaking&quot; powers he lacks full control over is accepted by 4R</li>
<li>The implied drug dealing - that is completely incompatible with 4Rs long-term goals</li>
<li>Acolyte Fels is an in-name-only-version of himself (side note: if you has asked, I would have made a full character profile so you'd get a better idea of his character.)</li>
<li>Demons are used in a manner that would not be accepted by Rass</li>
<li>Lack of explanation as to why either GoI would want to engage in a conflict</li>
</ul>
<p>I am aware that this was gonna be different, seeing as it is written by different authors from a different branch. But this just does not at all fit with the Fourth Reich as it is in the german branch. And the fact that some of the things I explained about 4R in chat (at the authors request) were forgotten or possibly even just ignored makes this especially hard to read.</p>
<p>To be honest, to me personally this seems less like you took a GOI and wrote a story with that GOI, and more like you had a story in mind and tried to force that GOI into the ideas you had for that story.</p>
<p>Sorry, but I can't give anything but a downvote, despite the fact that the tale itself is actually pretty good. But it, in my opinion, ignores the inherent challenge and the point of this contest: To take on the challenge of writing within the boundaries of a GoI from a different branch, instead of doing your own thing for the sake of it. This would have worked just as well (if not even better) as an Obskuracorps tale, so using a foreign GoI just seems &#8230; unnecessary to me.</p>

							</div>

								
